insert into `#__content` values ('31', 'Easter', '', '{mosimage} <br /> Part of our annual Easter celebration is to decorate the sanctuary with balloons and release them after the Easter Sunday service to the proclamations of &quot;He is risen - He is risen indeed!&quot; <br /><br />  Easter is the day Christians celebrate the resurrection of Jesus the Christ from the dead.<br /><br /> Easter is celebrated on the first Sunday following the first full moon after the Spring equinox which means the date of Easter can range between March 22 and April 25 depending on the lunar cycle. <br /><br />  Easter is the most openly joyful celebration of the church year. Celebrated after the darkness of Lent and Holy Week, this season is a living expression of the hope that God has brought into the world through the death and resurrection of Jesus.<br /><br />   The season from Easter to Pentecost is also called the Great Fifty Days, a tradition inspired by the Jewish season of fifty days between Passover and Shavuot&mdash;the feast celebrating the giving of the Torah to Moses. <br /><br />  The liturgical color for this season is celebratory White or Gold. When the season ends on Pentecost Sunday, White is replaced with Red. This color reminds the congregation of fire&mdash;the symbol of the Holy Spirit.  <span class=\"note\"><strong>Prayer:<br /> Forgive us, God, for our disbelief&mdash;for seeing an empty tomb and thinking a cruel trick; for discovering a discarded burial cloth yet still holding to death; for hearing words of life but keeping them to ourselves. Restore us even in our unbelief. Amen....<br /><br /> Assurance of Pardon:<br /> &quot;Do not be afraid; for see&mdash;I am bringing you good news of great joy for all the people: to you is born this day in the city of David a Savior, who is the Messiah, the Lord&rdquo; (Luke 2:10-11 NRSV) Do not be afraid! Receive the good news with great joy! God&rsquo;s promises are true. Christ has risen. Believe and be alive.<br />  - &copy;2007 Local Church Ministries, Worship and Education Ministry Team, United Church of Christ</strong> </span>', '', '1', '4', '0', '23', '2007-04-20 19:33:31', '62', '', '2007-05-28 20:57:35', '62', '0', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2007-04-20 19:30:47', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Easter042.jpg|center|Easter Service - Photo by Sue White|0||bottom||', '', 'pageclass_sfx=\nback_button=\nitem_title=1\nlink_titles=\nintrotext=1\nsection=0\nsection_link=0\ncategory=0\ncategory_link=0\nrating=\nauthor=\ncreatedate=\nmodifydate=\npdf=\nprint=\nemail=\nkeyref=\ndocbook_type=', '7', '0', '2', '', '', '0', '0');
