insert into `#__content` values ('73', 'The Family and Senior Homeless Initiative', '', 'February 17, 2007<br />Request for Funding Assistance<br /><br />Christ Congregational Church began its participation in The Family and Senior Homeless Initiative following a presentation in which Denver&rsquo;s Mayor, John Hickenlooper, shared that there are an estimated 4,693 homeless people in Denver in a one year period.&nbsp; Most are women and children.&nbsp; He issued a call to action.&nbsp; His challenge was for each faith community to adopt a homeless senior or family by providing the initial $1200 toward the first month&rsquo;s rent and deposit on housing.&nbsp; In addition, life skills mentoring and other assistance would be provided according specific needs of the senior or family. Our congregation immediately accepted his challenge. <br /><br />Our mission board asked the congregation, through a monthly offering, to fund the initial twelve hundred dollars to pay for a family&rsquo;s first month&rsquo;s rent and deposit. Following that collection, eight people volunteered to be mentors and received training.', '<p>After several months, we were matched with a woman who wanted live in our neighborhood.&nbsp; Several mentors met and talked with her. Through the Rescue Mission we paid her initial rent deposit of four hundred dollars.&nbsp; Unfortunately, after a few failed attempts to work with her, she dropped out of the program and we were unable to continue meeting with her. <br /> <br /> Not to be deterred from our mission, we were assigned another family with whom we have been meeting and talking regularly.&nbsp; This family is in a difficult situation.&nbsp; The father and 12 year old son have been diagnosed with bi-polar disorder. The 15 year old daughter also has special needs.&nbsp; The mother works non-stop to organize their daily lives: making sure the family members take necessary medication, arranging transportation to medical appointments and school.&nbsp; Through the Interfaith Hospitality Network the family has been staying in temporary housing. They stay one week in a particular church and then the following week move to a different church.&nbsp; The father has applied for Social Security Disability, but has not yet been approved.&nbsp; There is not enough sustainable income currently to rent an apartment.&nbsp; We will continue to work with the family to be able to find and stay in a home.<br /> <br /> &nbsp;Although the program is designed for a congregation to be paired with one family, there is a shortage of sponsoring congregations, so we were recently contacted and asked to mentor another family.&nbsp; This past week we met with an inspiring young woman who has a 10 year old daughter and two sons, ages 5 and 2.&nbsp; She has found a suitable rental. We were able to help with the deposit, first month&rsquo;s rent and some household items.&nbsp;&nbsp; She has many beneficial things happening in her life.&nbsp; We will continue to meet with her over the next several months to discuss budgeting, parenting and other areas of concern to her.<br /> <br /> The Family and Senior Initiative is designed to be a multi-year program.&nbsp; Although we have a group of people committed to continuing with the program, we know that our church may have difficulty supplying all the necessary funds. If the foundation is able to help support this effort, we would be grateful.<br /> <br /> Sincerely, <br /> Sandy Selzer<br />Homeless Initiative Working Group<br />Christ Congregational Church, UCC</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '1', '10', '0', '41', '2007-05-16 23:05:12', '62', '', '2007-05-16 23:15:25', '62', '0', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2007-05-16 23:02:27', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'pageclass_sfx=\nback_button=\nitem_title=1\nlink_titles=\nintrotext=1\nsection=0\nsection_link=0\ncategory=0\ncategory_link=0\nrating=\nauthor=\ncreatedate=\nmodifydate=\npdf=\nprint=\nemail=\nkeyref=\ndocbook_type=', '3', '0', '4', '', '', '0', '0');
