insert into `#__content` values ('74', 'Faith in Action - April 07 Update', '', 'Faith in Action<br />Family and Senior Homeless Initiative<br />April 2007 Update<br />&nbsp;<br />The two families we have been working with have both settled into their homes. The amount of support they have received from our congregation has been phenomenal.<br /><br />', 'One family is living near Irving and Hampden.&nbsp; Their apartment is close enough that the daughter can walk to Sheridan High School and the son is bussed to a special school in Littleton.&nbsp; We furnished almost their entire home.&nbsp; We provided them with living room, bedroom and kitchen furniture, linens, tvs, lamps, kitchen and bathroom items, and food.<br /> <br /> The second family is a single mother, ten year old daughter, and two sons who are two and five.&nbsp;&nbsp; She left a domestic abuse situation but was able to plan ahead enough to be able to take the majority of her furniture with her.&nbsp; We were able to quickly pay her deposit and first month&rsquo;s rent on a house near King St. and Evans. Then the most immediate need was to find separate beds for her sons because the youngest, who has asthma and difficulty sleeping, would keep the other son awake at night.&nbsp; She now has all the furniture she needs.&nbsp; We&rsquo;ve supplied her kitchen with glasses, dishes, baskets, linens and various utensils, as well as a vacuum cleaner. &nbsp;<br /> <br /> You donated so many cleaning, personal and household supplies that we have been able to divide the items between both families and help them stock their shelves.&nbsp;&nbsp; The mentoring team has been inspired by the strengths of the families, and will continue to meet with them on the challenges they face.&nbsp; Their future is looking much brighter because of your generosity.<br /> <br /> We recently received a large donation to help us with our &ldquo;next &ldquo; family. And for those of you who kindly offered monies to purchase necessary items for the families that weren&rsquo;t needed at this time, don&rsquo;t worry, we&rsquo;ll be keeping you in mind!<br /> <br /> Many thanks to all,<br /> <br /> Sandy Selzer<br />Homeless Initiative Working Group<br />Christ Congregational Church, UCC<br /> <br />&nbsp; ', '1', '10', '0', '41', '2007-05-16 23:24:59', '62', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0', '0', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2007-05-16 23:22:18', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'pageclass_sfx=\nback_button=\nitem_title=1\nlink_titles=\nintrotext=1\nsection=0\nsection_link=0\ncategory=0\ncategory_link=0\nrating=\nauthor=\ncreatedate=\nmodifydate=\npdf=\nprint=\nemail=\nkeyref=\ndocbook_type=', '1', '0', '3', '', '', '0', '0');
